        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30215",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you provide some reproduce code? A zip with a minimal directory structure showing the issue would help.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T06:11:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T06:11:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30221",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've been able to independently reproduce.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T07:43:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T07:43:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30222",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually... I can't confirm this. \n\nI created the following directory structure:\n{code}\napplication\/\n    Bootstrap.php\n    controllers\/\n    configs\/\n        application.ini\n    modules\/\n        foo\/\n            Bootstrap.php\n            controllers\/\n            models\/\n                User.php\n{code}\n\nMy application.ini had the following directives:\n\n{code}\n\nresources.frontController.controllerDirectory = APPLICATION_PATH \"\/controllers\"\nresources.frontController.moduleDirectory = APPLICATION_PATH \"\/modules\"\nresources.modules.foo = \"Bar\" ; to ensure modules resource is loaded\n{code}\n\nMy application\/modules\/foo\/Bootstrap.php file had the following:\n\n{code}\nclass Foo_Bootstrap extends Zend_Application_Module_Bootstrap\n{\n}\n{code}\n\napplication\/modules\/foo\/models\/User.php had the following:\n\n{code}\nclass Foo_Model_User\n{\n}\n{code}\n\nI then created a test.php file at the same level as application\/ with these contents:\n\n{code}\ndefine('APPLICATION_PATH', dirname(__FILE__) . '\/application');\n\n\/** Zend_Application *\/\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Application.php';  \n\n\/\/ Create application, bootstrap, and run\n$application = new Zend_Application(\n    'development', \n    APPLICATION_PATH . '\/configs\/application.ini'\n);\n$application->bootstrap();\n\n$model = new Foo_Model_User();\nvar_export($model);\n{code}\n\nThis worked exactly as expected -- autoloading for the Foo module was enabled, and I was able to load that class.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T08:30:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T08:30:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30223",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jamal",
                        "name": "jamal",
                        "displayName": "Jamal Fanaian",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Matthew, \n\nSorry, I should have supplied such an archive with my original submission. I will next time. I'm glad you were able to replicate it though. \n\nHere is what I ended up doing to work around the issue: http:\/\/pastie.org\/449891 ... It is mostly based on how the actual Resource Modules class works.\n\nLet me know if you need anything else.\n\nThank you very much!\nJamal Fanaian",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jamal",
                        "name": "jamal",
                        "displayName": "Jamal Fanaian",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T08:30:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T08:30:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30224",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jamal",
                        "name": "jamal",
                        "displayName": "Jamal Fanaian",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Alright, let me try to see if I can replicate the issue individually. Maybe I just made a mistake somewhere. I hope I'm not wasting your time though.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jamal",
                        "name": "jamal",
                        "displayName": "Jamal Fanaian",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T08:33:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T08:33:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30225",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "BTW, I was using the standard Modules resource available on trunk. Test against that when you attempt to reproduce. If you can reproduce it, re-open the issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T08:48:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T08:48:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30227",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jamal",
                        "name": "jamal",
                        "displayName": "Jamal Fanaian",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well I was able to actually get it working in a new project. So apparently I am doing something wrong. I'm using the same exact ZF library for both projects though (releases-1.8.0PR). Thanks for the help, I'll just keep working on it since it looks like it is an issue on my end. Sorry that I wasted your time with this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jamal",
                        "name": "jamal",
                        "displayName": "Jamal Fanaian",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T09:11:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T09:11:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30229",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No worries -- I'd rather find out about a possible bug than have it go unreported and later confirmed. :)\n\nGlad you were able to get it working, and I hope you figure out the issue in the original app.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T09:46:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T09:46:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30646",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joe-w3design",
                        "name": "joe-w3design",
                        "displayName": "Joe Conigliaro",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why does Zend_Application_Resource_Modules not not bootstrap the Default module?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joe-w3design",
                        "name": "joe-w3design",
                        "displayName": "Joe Conigliaro",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-04T09:52:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-04T09:52:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30650",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Because the assumption at the time of coding was that the application bootstrap would be from the default module. Several people have since indicated this is not the case, and we plan to accomodate separate application\/default module bootstraps later in the 1.8 series.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-04T11:33:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-04T11:33:12.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
